Class HerdWebDisplay

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.iastate.ansci.flip.extension.HerdWebDisplay

  • public class HerdWebDisplay
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that provides the methods to manage the animals being displayed to a web user Female and male animals are separately displayed

      • HerdWebDisplay

        public HerdWebDisplay(int populationID,
                      java.lang.String instructor,
                      java.util.ArrayList<Herd> herds,
                      int sourceData,
                      int animalsOrder,
                      UserBean userBean)
        Creates a new instance of a HerdWebDisplay object
        Parameters:
        populationID - : Identifier of the selected population
        instructor - : Username of the instructor accessing the selected population
        herds - : A selected list of Herd objects
        sourceData - : If this value is HerdWebDisplay.TEMPORAL, it means data is retrieved from temporal database, otherwise set it as HerdWebDisplay.PERSISTENT
        animalsOrder - : The order in which the animals of the selected population will be displayed on a web page.
        userBean - : The Session object of the instructor
